Merge branch 'klg/cross-testsuite.tags' into 'master'

Pass "target directory" to testsuite rather than "root directory"

See merge request eng/toolchain/aws!29

Pass "target directory" to testsuite rather than "root directory"

Our packaging scripts…

* set TARGET to Env().target.triplet at 'make setup' time, so testsuite.tags
is generated in a directory named after this triplet;

* run the testsuite launcher script directly from the 'regtests' folder,
bypassing Makefile:run_regtests which (via regtests/Makefile:aws_regtests)
might otherwise have changed to the correct directory.

Under these circumstances, the most straightforward solution seems to be
giving control back to our packaging scripts: they set TARGET, ergo they
control the directory for testsuite.tags, ergo they should pass that
information back to the testsuite runner.

Arguably this could be fixed by having 'AWSTestsuite.set_up' use the correct
compiler to locate 'build_dir' (our cross-compilers include the target
triplet in their name; "gcc -dumpmachine" will only ever return the native
triplet); it seems inelegant however to have testsuite.py use this
heuristic, but not makefile.conf.

Rework build setup to allow for out-of-tree build.

This rework make it possible to build in-tree as before:

   $ make setup
   $ make

And from another directory (out-of-tree build):

   $ cd <build-dir>
   $ make -C ../aws BLD_DIR=$PWD setup
   $ make -C ../aws BLD_DIR=$PWD

To build the demos:

   $ make -C ../aws/demos BLD_DIR=$PWD

Support for the testsuite has also been reworked to use the out-of-tree
build when needed:

   $ make -C ../aws BLD_DIR=$PWD run_regtests
